Key Match Events: Adam Zampa took four wickets for 47 runs, causing Sri Lanka to lose nine wickets for 52 runs and get bundled out for 209.
Mitchell Marsh scored 52 runs off 51 balls with 9 fours, regaining his form.
Australia won the match by five wickets against Sri Lanka.
Miscellaneous Highlights: A dust storm and rain interrupted the match, but Australia managed to secure a win.
Sri Lanka suffered their third successive defeat in the tournament.
